;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131170248.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US President Trump has ignited controversy by tweeting a provocative map aimed at Iran, declaring that 'the clock is ticking' in reference to potential military engagement. This revelation comes on the heels of his discussions with Israeli PM Netanyahu, signaling escalating tensions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/trumps-cryptic-gulf-map-with-red-arrows-at-iran-sparks-fresh-war-fears/articleshow/131170248.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/trumps-cryptic-gulf-map-with-red-arrows-at-iran-sparks-fresh-war-fears/articleshow/131170248.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-18T13:34:53+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131170623,imgsize-1087528.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US, Nigeria launch fresh kinetic strikes on ISIS targets]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131170707.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US Africa Command, in coordination with Nigeria, conducted kinetic strikes against ISIS militants in Northeastern Nigeria. This operation follows the recent killing of a top ISIS leader, Abu-Bilal al-Minuki, in a joint US-Nigerian mission. The strikes aim to diminish ISIS's capacity to plan attacks threatening regional and US security.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/us-nigeria-launch-fresh-kinetic-strikes-on-isis-targets/articleshow/131170707.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/us-nigeria-launch-fresh-kinetic-strikes-on-isis-targets/articleshow/131170707.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-18T13:39:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131170746,imgsize-25200.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Strong earthquake hits southwest China, thousands evacuated after buildings damaged]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131169397.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Guangxi region of southwest China experienced a severe 5.2-magnitude earthquake, leaving its mark with structural damages and disruption to vital services. Thousands were forced to evacuate as the tremors rattled homes and offices alike. Tragically, authorities reported two lives lost and one individual unaccounted for, prompting active rescue missions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/strong-earthquake-hits-southwest-china-thousands-evacuated-after-buildings-damaged/articleshow/131169397.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/strong-earthquake-hits-southwest-china-thousands-evacuated-after-buildings-damaged/articleshow/131169397.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-18T12:56:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131169820,imgsize-112602.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘I am calling from the police’: UK pensioners lose thousands in fake officer scam, authorities issue urgent warning]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131170177.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Elderly Britons are losing thousands to sophisticated scams where criminals pose as police and bank investigators. Victims are manipulated into revealing sensitive financial details or handing over bank cards to "couriers." Authorities urge extreme caution with unexpected calls involving money, emphasizing that genuine officials never request such information.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/i-am-calling-from-the-police-uk-pensioners-lose-thousands-in-fake-officer-scam-authorities-issue-urgent-warning/articleshow/131170177.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/i-am-calling-from-the-police-uk-pensioners-lose-thousands-in-fake-officer-scam-authorities-issue-urgent-warning/articleshow/131170177.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-18T13:13:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131170156,imgsize-28312.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[London tube strike confirmed after last-minute talks collapse, 4 days of disruption expected]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131169494.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[London faces significant travel disruption as RMT union members strike for four days over a proposed voluntary four-day working week for Tube drivers. Talks between Transport for London and the RMT failed, leading to planned walkouts from May 19-22, impacting services and causing potential overcrowding on alternative transport.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/london-tube-strike-confirmed-after-last-minute-talks-collapse-4-days-of-disruption-expected/articleshow/131169494.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/london-tube-strike-confirmed-after-last-minute-talks-collapse-4-days-of-disruption-expected/articleshow/131169494.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-18T12:46:30+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131169588,imgsize-291600.cms"/></